<div id='communityQuestionsWithAnswers'>
<div class='communityQuestionAndAnswer'>
<div class='communityQuestion'>
<div class='questionText'>
<a href="/questions/1303359-why-is-nothing-mentioned-about">Why is nothing mentioned about Rutherfurd&#39;s use of corn as a crop in Sarum during pre-historic times when corn is a new world crop? It did not exist in Europe, Asia or Africa. I would love to see it corrected in later editions...or at least a mention of a few factual errors.</a>
</div>
<div class='communityQAFooter questionFooter'>
<ul class='questionFooterActions'>
<li class='footerItem like'>
<span class='likeItContainer' id='like_container_community_question_1303359'><a id="like_count_community_question_1303359" rel="nofollow" href="/rating/voters/1303359?resource_type=CommunityQuestion"><span class="likesCount">1 like</span></a>&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;<a rel="nofollow" class="jsLike like_it" href="https://www.goodreads.com/user/new?remember=true&amp;return_url=%2Fbook%2Fshow%2F1853145.Sarum">like</a></span>

</li>
<li class='footerItem communityQuestionTimestamp'>
<a href="/questions/1303359-why-is-nothing-mentioned-about">3 years ago</a>
</li>
<li class='footerItem communityQuestionPermalink'>
<a href="/questions/1303359-why-is-nothing-mentioned-about">See all 7 answers</a>
</li>
</ul>
</div>

</div>
<div class='allCommunityAnswers'>
<div class='communityAnswer'>
<div class='communityAnswerBody'>
<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/68140404-steph"><img alt="" src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/users/1501299152i/68140404._UY100_CR16,0,100,100_.jpg" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/68140404-steph">Steph</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">In the beginning of the book, he states that he uses the word &quot;corn&quot; to be a &quot;generic term for cereal&quot;. <a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">In the beginning of the book, he states that he uses the word "corn" to be a "generic term for cereal". <a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
</span>
</div>
</div>
