  <span id="freeText541719637097000086" style="display:none">It took me a long time to read this one, it's huge but worth it. It's a history lesson disguised as fiction, and it's gorgeous.<br /><br />The book follows five families from prehistoric to modern day, jumping through some of the most important moments in the history of Sarum and England. The last two chapters were the most heart wrenching for me, but there are a lot of moments like that. Rutherford doesn't try to make it happily ever after, it's real life and believeable.<br /><br />I can't wait to get started on his others, but I'm going to pick a slightly less meaty volume to work on next!</span>
