              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/5553160-bodosika-bodosika?shelf=england">england</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3944017134" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer14204852719057554459">Title: Sarum<br/>Author: Edward Rutherfurd<br/>Date published :May 1987<br/>Pages: 1033<br/><br/>The author traces the history of Sarum/Salisbury area of England from pre historical ice age to present day through the eyes of five families using interesting and colorful characters that span many generations.<br/>Though it was a historical fiction and voluminous (1033 pages) It was worth the time.<br/>This is my first book by Edward Rutherfurd and it will not be my last because i really enjoyed it and I believe that anyone that enj</span>
  <span id="freeText14204852719057554459" style="display:none">Title: Sarum<br />Author: Edward Rutherfurd<br />Date published :May 1987<br />Pages: 1033<br /><br />The author traces the history of Sarum/Salisbury area of England from pre historical ice age to present day through the eyes of five families using interesting and colorful characters that span many generations.<br />Though it was a historical fiction and voluminous (1033 pages) It was worth the time.<br />This is my first book by Edward Rutherfurd and it will not be my last because i really enjoyed it and I believe that anyone that enjoy historical fiction and books written by James Meschner, James Clavell, and Leon Uris will definitely enjoy this.<br />4 Stars</span>
  <a data-text-id="14204852719057554459" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

